00:37:35.599 --> 00:37:40.720
right. If you look at just polling information,
it's not just whether it's Republicans or

00:37:40.720 --> 00:37:46.420
Democrats. People are just sick of the whole
group. And they lump the group together.

00:37:46.420 --> 00:37:52.279
And whether it's the President or Congress,
it's all of a piece. In terms of what social

00:37:52.279 --> 00:37:55.470
media, I don't know. I think you guys probably
know that better than what I do. I'm still

00:37:55.470 --> 00:37:57.660
figuring out my little YouTube channel.

00:37:57.660 --> 00:38:02.313
[laughter]
But I do think social media--. I mean, I just

00:38:02.313 --> 00:38:09.779
think the ability to have conversations and
link people from different walks of life together

00:38:09.779 --> 00:38:14.950
in an online experience and give you direct
contact to people in Washington, I think is

00:38:14.950 --> 00:38:15.950
a unique thing.

00:38:15.950 --> 00:38:21.420
It used to be you'd have to write-in to your
Congressman or call them up. And you have

00:38:21.420 --> 00:38:25.950
the ability now to have much more direct links
and communication with their offices with

00:38:25.950 --> 00:38:31.930
them if they are online. And I think that
does really have an impact. I mean, I read

00:38:31.930 --> 00:38:36.950
my viewers tweets and email comments and comments
on the YouTube channel.

00:38:36.950 --> 00:38:40.660
I read them every single day, several times
a day. It's often the first thing I read waking

00:38:40.660 --> 00:38:44.930
up in the morning after I read the news headlines
and the last thing I read going to bed to

00:38:44.930 --> 00:38:50.390
respond to. And it really does have an impact.
I mean, I don't think you can underestimate

00:38:50.390 --> 00:38:52.720
the impact hearing directly from people has.

00:38:52.720 --> 00:38:54.970
