00:41:06.299 --> 00:41:07.609
been away from your workstations--.

00:41:07.609 --> 00:41:08.609
[laughter]

00:41:08.609 --> 00:41:12.920
You've all been locked out and fired.

00:41:12.920 --> 00:41:13.920
[laughter]

00:41:13.920 --> 00:41:18.740
I really don't know and that's, I think, what's
exciting. It's scary for some people, but

00:41:18.740 --> 00:41:26.700
I find it exciting. And I think, how will
the sharing of information change things?

00:41:26.700 --> 00:41:32.099
Will we need broadcast networks? Will we need
cable networks, news networks? Will everything

00:41:32.099 --> 00:41:38.609
be online? Will we need television anchors?
That's why I'm getting a day job, frankly,

00:41:38.609 --> 00:41:40.480
in case that happens.
[laughter]

00:41:40.480 --> 00:41:45.380
But I do think that's, I think anyone who
pretends to know where its going has no idea.

00:41:45.380 --> 00:41:49.180
I mean, I've talked to the people who run
these companies and I don't think they have

00:41:49.180 --> 00:41:54.839
a firm grasp of exactly where it's going.
So, I think right now, I can tell you CNN

00:41:54.839 --> 00:42:00.710
has certainly trying to be on as many platforms
as possible, on as many delivery systems as

00:42:00.710 --> 00:42:09.589
possible, to see what comes down the pike
and which one explodes, which one goes away.

00:42:09.589 --> 00:42:15.520
I do think that we're able to get information
from more sources than ever before and I think

00:42:15.520 --> 00:42:21.180
that's been a fantastic thing. There's a danger,
I think, in it in not knowing where the information

00:42:21.180 --> 00:42:25.950
really is coming from and being in this echo
chamber where something is inserted online,

00:42:25.950 --> 00:42:31.390
something appears online and then it's picked
up by other, and it becomes real even though

00:42:31.390 --> 00:42:32.390
it's not real.

00:42:32.390 --> 00:42:37.150
And so, I do think it matters where the information
comes from and whether that information has

00:42:37.150 --> 00:42:42.700
been checked and vetted. We all know it. We've
all seen in Presidential elections and just

00:42:42.700 --> 00:42:46.130
in news in general how stories take on a life
of their own.

00:42:46.130 --> 00:42:52.920
I don't know if you remember the story about
President Obama going to India recently and

00:42:52.920 --> 00:42:56.520
there was this story going around that his
trip was gonna cost, I don't know, it was

00:42:56.520 --> 00:43:01.700
like 200 million dollars a day, or something.
And it was being repeated on radio stations,

00:43:01.700 --> 00:43:06.220
especially conservative radio stations, but
on television stations and it became--.

00:43:06.220 --> 00:43:13.710
I have Michelle Bachman on my program saying
this as fact. And I was like, "Where does

00:43:13.710 --> 00:43:16.599
this figure come from?" And she was like,
"Well, it's being reported in the media."

00:43:16.599 --> 00:43:21.500
Which, that doesn't mean anything. That's
like saying, "I found it on the street."

00:43:21.500 --> 00:43:22.500
[laughter]

00:43:22.500 --> 00:43:29.410
So, we started checking and going back and
we traced it back to an unnamed Indian provincial

00:43:29.410 --> 00:43:36.829
government official quoted in a local Indian
paper. So, the credibility of that is, it

00:43:36.829 --> 00:43:37.829
just doesn't mean anything.

00:43:37.829 --> 00:43:44.150
Why would a provincial Indian government official,
unnamed, in a local paper know how much President

00:43:44.150 --> 00:43:48.289
Obama's security costs were when the White
House doesn't even release that information?

00:43:48.289 --> 00:43:52.829
And the war in Iraq costs, I don't know, 190
million dollars. So, it just didn't make any

00:43:52.829 --> 00:43:54.269
sense.

00:43:54.269 --> 00:43:58.769
So, we were able to just debunk that, but
it had taken on a life of its own. So, I do

00:43:58.769 --> 00:44:03.400
think it's important, even in this age where
information is more easily shared and more

00:44:03.400 --> 00:44:09.230
easily accessible, that even no matter where
it goes, that I think there will be some need

00:44:09.230 --> 00:44:15.329
for, I don't wanna say gate keepers but for
vetting the information. And how that happens,

00:44:15.329 --> 00:44:19.490
whether you need the companies that currently
exist or whether it's some kind of new structure

00:44:19.490 --> 00:44:26.400
or just individuals who are responsible. I
mean, I go to websites that I think I'd trust

00:44:26.400 --> 00:44:30.370
or I think I value the opinion of the person
who's running those websites and I think they

00:44:30.370 --> 00:44:32.950
have certain standards.

00:44:32.950 --> 00:44:39.190
And I think everybody has to come up in their
own mind with what they believe and what sources

00:44:39.190 --> 00:44:40.190
they actually trust.

